CatDescriptText: Mrs. Elizabeth McKenzie, 2550 Centre Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 9, 1957, pg. 2 with question: "Do you believe that licensed taverns are as harmful to a neighborhood as speakeasies and gambling joints? Why?" answer reads: "I believe that speakeasies and gambling joints are more harmful than taverns because I think that taverns are open to the public.  Young folks can be in there, who the public and the parents don't know anything about."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Elizabeth McKenzie, wearing light colored coat with rounded collar and drop earrings, standing in front of chain link fence, possibly in front of Bedford Dwellings
